FAQ.question: What is the difference between translation and transliteration?
FAQ.answer: A translation tells you the meaning of words in another language. While a transliteration does not reveal the meaning of the words, it can help you pronounce them correctly. Transliteration changes the letters from one alphabet or language into the corresponding, similar-sounding characters of another alphabet. Therefore, we can say, transliteration changes the letters from one alphabet into the similar-sounding characters of another alphabet. This makes it the simplest and fastest method of typing in pangungusap without practicing any pangungusap keyboard. You can either use the Google input tool for FREE.
